WEBVTT

00:06.464 --> 00:08.425
[opening theme music playing]

00:49.299 --> 00:51.968
STILL SHINING

01:11.571 --> 01:13.031
ACCESS

01:13.615 --> 01:15.825
The changing room
is down the hall on the right.

01:15.909 --> 01:17.619
You can put on a uniform in your size.

01:18.328 --> 01:20.121
Did you bring a pair of black flats?

01:20.205 --> 01:21.206
Yes.

01:21.998 --> 01:23.208
You may go in.

01:23.291 --> 01:25.293
[pleasant music playing]

01:26.503 --> 01:28.129
CHANGING ROOM

01:28.671 --> 01:30.089
Work starts at 2:00 p.m.

01:30.173 --> 01:32.217
So we'll move at 1:55 p.m.

01:32.300 --> 01:33.301
[trainees] Yes, ma'am.

01:42.101 --> 01:43.686
[staff] Could you try these on?

01:43.770 --> 01:44.771
[trainees] Okay.

02:07.252 --> 02:14.217
STILL SHINING

02:18.054 --> 02:18.888
[grunts]

02:28.064 --> 02:29.566
When are the guests leaving?

02:30.900 --> 02:31.901
In 30 or 40 minutes.

02:33.153 --> 02:34.571
How was the work?

02:35.321 --> 02:37.115
[sighs] It was hard,

02:37.198 --> 02:39.617
but it was fun. [chuckles]

02:40.201 --> 02:41.035
Ugh…

02:42.078 --> 02:43.246
Geez, I'm tired.

02:44.330 --> 02:45.540
[groans]

02:47.041 --> 02:48.251
[sighs]

02:49.460 --> 02:51.880
So this is what it looks like from here.

02:51.963 --> 02:54.507
I can see the mountains.

02:54.591 --> 02:56.342
And the sunset too.

02:58.344 --> 03:02.849
I'll work part-time on weekends for now.
Then, I'll decide to take time off or not.

03:03.892 --> 03:05.560
You should once you're an intern.

03:06.227 --> 03:07.604
Apply for the summer internship.

03:10.815 --> 03:14.527
When you become an intern,
you can move into the residence hall.

03:16.362 --> 03:18.281
-What's that?
-[Seong-chan] The dorms.

03:19.699 --> 03:20.700
The dorms?

03:22.785 --> 03:25.121
You can dorm once you become an intern.

03:25.204 --> 03:27.290
How long is the internship?

03:27.373 --> 03:28.875
It depends.

03:28.958 --> 03:32.253
It can be for summer vacation,
for half a year, or for even a year.

03:33.212 --> 03:35.632
If they're providing housing
in dorms… [exclaims]

03:36.174 --> 03:38.885
the internship must be long and tough.

03:39.552 --> 03:41.054
I might take a break from school.

03:41.930 --> 03:43.389
Have you selected a department yet?

03:43.473 --> 03:45.350
Mmm… Not yet.

03:45.934 --> 03:47.727
Should I take
the first position that opens?

03:48.478 --> 03:49.312
If possible,

03:50.355 --> 03:52.357
I hope you get the position you want.

03:53.149 --> 03:54.150
The position I want?

03:56.236 --> 03:57.820
[lighthearted music playing]

03:57.904 --> 03:59.739
I'll ask what departments they have.

04:00.865 --> 04:02.533
I'm happy just thinking about it.

04:04.410 --> 04:05.703
Mmm…

04:06.996 --> 04:08.665
You're good at English,

04:08.748 --> 04:10.708
you like people,

04:10.792 --> 04:12.460
and you draw vegetables well.

04:12.543 --> 04:14.671
I told you there was a job for you.
[chuckles softly]

04:14.754 --> 04:17.799
Geez. I can't believe you remember that.

04:24.764 --> 04:28.017
Vegetable drawings
are probably going to be useless.

04:29.602 --> 04:31.688
I hope it's somewhere I can speak English.

04:31.771 --> 04:33.564
I'm good at casual small talk.

04:33.648 --> 04:36.067
Before So-hyeon was around,
I used to talk with guests

04:36.150 --> 04:38.111
when there weren't too many of them.

04:38.194 --> 04:40.446
I can speak English with confidence.
Impressive, right?

04:40.530 --> 04:42.573
[laughing] You're all excited.

04:42.657 --> 04:44.784
[chuckling] I am.

04:46.077 --> 04:48.329
My dream of becoming independent
felt uncertain,

04:48.413 --> 04:50.164
but it's feeling more concrete now.

04:51.165 --> 04:52.750
I guess this is what opportunity is.

04:55.086 --> 04:56.212
[sighs softly]

05:02.844 --> 05:06.097
I only work on weekends for now,
but I'll gradually start working weekdays.

05:07.098 --> 05:08.599
I'm free only on the weekends though.

05:09.392 --> 05:12.437
-Matching our schedules might be…
-How about Friday nights?

05:13.980 --> 05:16.357
-Let's work it out.
-Yeah.

05:18.359 --> 05:21.154
When it's destiny, it's not vague.

05:21.237 --> 05:23.406
It's clear. You don't hesitate about it.

05:24.490 --> 05:28.161
I guess that's how people find
direction in life and move forward.

05:29.245 --> 05:32.165
I'm curious. In what way is it clear?

05:32.248 --> 05:34.459
Mmm… You can feel it.

05:34.542 --> 05:37.587
Because of you,
I know what destiny feels like.

05:39.922 --> 05:41.549
Why don't I know it then?

05:41.632 --> 05:45.094
Mmm… As soon as
you see something, bam, boom!

05:45.178 --> 05:48.306
It feels strong and clear.
Try to think back.

05:50.391 --> 05:51.476
Bam? Boom?

05:52.643 --> 05:53.936
I've felt that so many times.

05:54.687 --> 05:55.897
When did you feel it?

05:59.901 --> 06:01.736
What? When was it?

06:03.446 --> 06:07.241
When you stumbled
as if you were about to faint

06:07.325 --> 06:09.035
while walking across the schoolyard.

06:09.702 --> 06:12.330
Me? Come on. I've never stumbled-- Oh.

06:13.206 --> 06:15.166
Sorry. Was that too strong?

06:16.084 --> 06:17.126
[Eun-a] Hey!

06:17.919 --> 06:20.838
I guess you're okay with me
going home alone now?

06:21.839 --> 06:22.840
Does it upset you?

06:24.592 --> 06:25.593
A little.

06:26.928 --> 06:28.054
Nice job adapting.

06:28.137 --> 06:29.472
[in English] Bye.

06:36.354 --> 06:38.356
[pleasant music playing]

06:48.157 --> 06:49.867
[in Korean] I'll come down Saturday night.

06:50.952 --> 06:55.498
Uh… If I leave right after tutoring,
it'll be around 11:00 p.m. And…

06:57.416 --> 06:59.418
I've never felt comfortable

06:59.502 --> 07:01.212
seeing you leave alone.

07:02.213 --> 07:03.214
Okay?

07:13.724 --> 07:16.060
[mumbling] "I hope you enjoy
your time here."

07:19.021 --> 07:22.358
"I hope you enjoy your time here."
Your time here?

07:24.569 --> 07:25.570
"Your time here."

07:26.279 --> 07:27.780
We'll head out onto the floor.

07:27.864 --> 07:29.073
[trainees] Yes, ma'am.

07:42.253 --> 07:43.504
The guests are still here.

07:44.255 --> 07:45.715
Okay. Have a good one.

07:48.759 --> 07:50.845
SAINT OCEAN HOTEL
SUMMER INTERNSHIP PROGRAM

07:50.928 --> 07:53.347
INTERNSHIP BENEFITS
FREE DORMITORY ACCOMMODATION

07:53.431 --> 07:54.474
[clicks tongue]

07:57.310 --> 07:58.519
[sighs]

08:04.108 --> 08:06.736
[sighs] I'm so exhausted.

08:08.446 --> 08:09.447
[sighs]

08:10.072 --> 08:12.241
But it's so much fun.

08:16.787 --> 08:17.622
<i>Tae-seo.</i>

08:50.029 --> 08:51.072
[So-hyeon] How's the food?

08:51.155 --> 08:53.908
-[man] It's well-arranged and delicious.
-[So-hyeon] Thank you.

08:53.991 --> 08:56.410
-[Seon-gyu] Is there anything you need?
-[man] There's so much food.

08:56.494 --> 08:58.704
-[man] We'll let you know.
-[woman] Thanks for the food.

08:58.788 --> 08:59.914
[man] Let's try them in order.

08:59.997 --> 09:01.999
[lighthearted music playing]

09:12.677 --> 09:13.970
Shh.

09:15.513 --> 09:16.806
[mouthing] I'm coming in.

09:46.752 --> 09:49.213
I think Eun-a's exhausted.

09:49.964 --> 09:51.424
The work must be hard.

09:52.174 --> 09:53.175
I don't know.

09:53.801 --> 09:54.760
Ask her yourself.

09:56.220 --> 09:57.597
She won't tell me.

09:58.764 --> 10:00.975
This was cooked really nicely.

10:01.058 --> 10:02.810
Could you take some to her
before it's gone?

10:02.893 --> 10:04.770
Wait. Will she hate it
because it's fattening?

10:06.397 --> 10:08.858
They're asking for me.
You should take it to her yourself.

10:08.941 --> 10:10.651
[hesitates] She won't eat it if I do.

10:10.735 --> 10:11.902
Don't be intimidated by her.

10:13.029 --> 10:15.781
Check in on her and ask her everything.

10:23.331 --> 10:24.373
[Tae-seo] Hold still.

10:24.457 --> 10:26.250
-[Eun-a] What?
-[Tae-seo] Is that it?

10:27.043 --> 10:29.378
[lock clacking]

10:30.212 --> 10:31.047
Eun-a.

10:32.006 --> 10:33.090
Eun-a!

10:38.054 --> 10:39.305
[amusing music playing]

10:42.058 --> 10:44.852
[So-hyeon] Why were you
hiding your relationship?

10:45.978 --> 10:48.939
[spluttering] We started seeing each other
during senior year,

10:49.023 --> 10:51.025
so we didn't want our families to worry.

10:51.651 --> 10:55.321
There's no need to hide it anymore,
but I guess we got used to it.

10:56.113 --> 10:57.573
We won't do that anymore.

10:57.657 --> 10:58.991
[Eun-a] We're fine on our own.

10:59.075 --> 11:00.951
Can you just come down and talk to us?

11:02.370 --> 11:03.204
[sighs]

11:04.872 --> 11:06.332
I understand.

11:06.999 --> 11:09.168
It's a small town,
so they'd just gossip about it.

11:09.794 --> 11:10.795
[Tae-seo] That's right.

11:12.463 --> 11:14.882
Okay, let's keep it a secret.
I'll stay quiet too.

11:16.926 --> 11:18.594
You're using contraception, right?

11:20.721 --> 11:22.556
We haven't done…

11:24.392 --> 11:25.976
Well, be careful in the future.

11:26.060 --> 11:29.230
Don't try to act like my mom, So-hyeon.

11:29.313 --> 11:30.481
Did I say something wrong?

11:31.148 --> 11:32.733
You're 20 years old now.

11:32.817 --> 11:34.068
You're not young anymore.

11:34.652 --> 11:36.320
You should be careful about these things.

11:38.572 --> 11:39.657
[sighs softly]

12:03.764 --> 12:04.765
So damn embarrassing.

12:17.570 --> 12:18.696
You're something else.

12:18.779 --> 12:22.658
You don't even pry or tell me what to do.

12:23.993 --> 12:26.328
How can I tell you what to do?

12:27.163 --> 12:29.665
All I can do is wait
until you feel better.

12:38.883 --> 12:40.342
She's going to marry my dad.

12:41.469 --> 12:43.012
I like that my dad's getting married.

12:44.305 --> 12:46.474
But I don't know
what kind of person she is.

12:47.766 --> 12:50.978
She says she was born in Hawaii,
but she speaks fluent Korean.

12:51.061 --> 12:52.521
Sometimes, I think she's a scammer.

12:54.190 --> 12:56.525
But she goes harvesting
vegetables with Dad

12:56.609 --> 12:58.027
and gladly does all the hard work.

12:59.111 --> 13:01.989
One moment, I feel like it's good
that Dad has someone like her.

13:02.740 --> 13:03.991
Then the next moment, I don't.

13:06.202 --> 13:07.203
Anyway,

13:07.286 --> 13:08.621
I feel uneasy at home.

13:09.538 --> 13:11.123
I should hurry and move out.

13:14.126 --> 13:15.836
Does that answer all the questions

13:16.921 --> 13:18.088
in your head?

13:22.593 --> 13:23.594
It's just…

13:24.512 --> 13:27.056
I only want to tell you
about nice and happy things.

13:27.932 --> 13:29.391
I try not to talk about my problems.

13:30.351 --> 13:32.603
Do I seem like
I'm still having a hard time?

13:34.647 --> 13:35.856
No.

13:37.566 --> 13:38.609
But I don't know.

13:40.194 --> 13:42.613
I end up telling you everything anyway.

13:44.240 --> 13:45.241
Eun-a,

13:48.160 --> 13:49.203
I'm all right.

13:51.747 --> 13:55.251
You can tell me right away
when things are tough.

13:57.169 --> 14:00.130
Tell me when you feel lost, not after.

14:00.839 --> 14:02.883
Tell me even if I might not have
the right answer.

14:06.720 --> 14:07.721
I'll do that.

14:12.768 --> 14:14.770
[slow romantic music playing]

14:16.021 --> 14:17.439
Look at me, Eun-a.

14:18.691 --> 14:21.652
You said you felt at ease
when you looked at me.

14:21.735 --> 14:22.778
Look.

15:07.489 --> 15:14.455
JUNE

15:16.415 --> 15:19.501
[teaching assistant] I started writing
my paper, but it's still a draft.

15:19.585 --> 15:22.504
Since it's about AI controllers,
it's interesting.

15:23.130 --> 15:26.258
Which AI learning method are you using?

15:26.342 --> 15:28.177
The reinforcement learning method.

15:28.260 --> 15:31.263
Ah, I'm reading a paper about that.
Want me to look it up?

15:31.931 --> 15:32.973
That'd be great.

15:33.557 --> 15:36.602
[inhales sharply]
Want to come to our lab during vacation?

15:37.186 --> 15:38.938
It's fun studying there during vacation.

15:40.272 --> 15:42.608
You might be able to become
a lab member too.

15:43.317 --> 15:44.610
You'll go to grad school anyway.

15:45.778 --> 15:48.072
-I haven't thought about it.
-[teaching assistant] Really?

15:48.155 --> 15:51.116
You're an academic type.
People like you end up in labs.

15:51.951 --> 15:53.285
What kind of person am I?

15:53.369 --> 15:54.662
You?

15:54.745 --> 15:56.622
You understand equations
in a physical sense.

15:56.705 --> 15:59.792
Those who try to grasp meanings
fixate on the nature of things.

16:00.376 --> 16:01.502
You should do what you like.

16:04.421 --> 16:08.217
Can liking something
be the basis for everything one does?

16:08.968 --> 16:10.970
Of course. What else would it be?

16:13.222 --> 16:16.850
One's condition, situation,
or responsibilities?

16:19.061 --> 16:20.229
That's refreshing to hear.

16:20.813 --> 16:22.731
No one decides their future
on those these days.

16:22.815 --> 16:24.108
They only focus on themselves.

16:25.317 --> 16:27.945
Anyway, come join us this summer.

16:30.406 --> 16:32.574
[chuckling] Hey, we don't let
just anyone join our lab.

16:32.658 --> 16:34.201
[chuckling] I know.

16:36.578 --> 16:38.247
Can I keep reading it?

16:38.330 --> 16:39.665
Of course. You're our ace.

16:40.624 --> 16:42.960
-I'm going to go see the professor.
-Okay. Thank you.

16:43.043 --> 16:43.877
Sure.

17:07.568 --> 17:08.777
[phone vibrates]

17:11.238 --> 17:13.115
[Eun-a] <i>What are you up to?</i>
<i>Are you in class?</i>

17:13.782 --> 17:15.743
[Tae-seo] <i>I have a free period,</i>
<i>so I'm in the lab.</i>

17:16.368 --> 17:17.703
[Eun-a] <i>When should we meet?</i>

17:18.370 --> 17:20.622
[Tae-seo] <i>Let's match our schedules.</i>
<i>When's good for you?</i>

17:20.706 --> 17:21.707
[phone vibrates]

17:24.418 --> 17:25.961
[Eun-a] <i>How about Wednesday evening?</i>

17:26.628 --> 17:29.548
[Tae-seo] <i>I have tutoring that</i>
<i>I can't reschedule. Exams are coming soon.</i>

17:30.340 --> 17:32.468
[Eun-a] <i>I get off work</i>
<i>at 7:00 p.m. on Friday.</i>

17:32.551 --> 17:34.136
<i>I'm working Saturday afternoon.</i>

17:34.845 --> 17:36.221
<i>What about Saturday morning?</i>

17:36.305 --> 17:40.142
SATURDAY
PREPARE FOR FINALS

17:40.684 --> 17:41.518
[Tae-seo] <i>Mmm…</i>

17:41.602 --> 17:43.937
<i>It works. I'll come to you.</i>

17:49.651 --> 17:51.320
[phone vibrating]

17:51.403 --> 17:53.155
SEONG-CHAN

18:03.457 --> 18:04.958
[phone continues vibrating]

18:08.337 --> 18:10.506
-Yes?
-[Seong-chan] <i>Are you still at the hotel?</i>

18:11.090 --> 18:13.092
The GRO team is looking for an intern.

18:14.009 --> 18:15.302
What's GRO?

18:15.385 --> 18:17.638
[Seong-chan] <i>Uh…</i>
<i>It's basically working the VIP lounge.</i>

18:17.721 --> 18:19.681
<i>You might have the upper hand.</i>

18:19.765 --> 18:22.392
The guests here often go to your place.

18:23.018 --> 18:24.895
<i>This department might fit you well.</i>

18:25.479 --> 18:26.605
It's perfect.

18:27.481 --> 18:29.024
<i>I'm pretty familiar with my guests.</i>

18:30.025 --> 18:31.443
That's why I'm recommending it.

18:31.527 --> 18:33.112
Go to the second floor.

18:33.195 --> 18:35.405
Introduce yourself
to the team leader, Yun Da-jeong.

18:35.489 --> 18:37.658
<i>She'll know your place well.</i>

18:37.741 --> 18:39.827
<i>And tell her you're here</i>
<i>as a part-time worker.</i>

18:43.413 --> 18:44.873
-[man] Ms. Yun.
-[Da-jeong] Yes?

18:44.957 --> 18:47.209
-Guests are waiting downstairs.
-Okay. Thanks.

18:51.588 --> 18:53.715
Hello, ma'am. I'm Mo Eun-a.

18:53.799 --> 18:54.842
Right.

18:54.925 --> 18:56.593
Seong-chan told me about you.

18:57.344 --> 18:59.138
I'm working part-time at the banquet hall.

19:02.891 --> 19:04.977
I'll get going then.

19:05.727 --> 19:07.062
All right.

19:13.360 --> 19:15.904
Right. Are you free this Saturday morning?

19:15.988 --> 19:17.489
My team needs a part-timer.

19:17.573 --> 19:18.782
Yes, I'm free.

19:19.366 --> 19:20.367
See you then.

19:26.206 --> 19:27.249
Right, Tae-seo.

19:34.464 --> 19:35.632
[Da-jeong] Ah, hello.

19:37.426 --> 19:38.719
Please come this way.

19:39.344 --> 19:41.346
[soft pensive music playing]

19:43.724 --> 19:45.017
Last time, we learned

19:45.100 --> 19:47.352
-about Fleming's Left-Hand Rule, right?
-Yes.

19:47.436 --> 19:48.604
This question's about that.

19:48.687 --> 19:50.272
The direction of rotation is plus…

19:50.355 --> 19:52.065
-[woman] Mr. Yeon.
-Yes?

19:52.149 --> 19:54.067
-[mouthing]
-[Tae-seo] Just a second.

19:55.360 --> 19:56.695
Yes?

19:56.778 --> 19:58.572
Should I book you for Saturday morning?

20:00.032 --> 20:01.033
Well…

20:01.950 --> 20:03.619
I'm going home on Saturday.

20:04.703 --> 20:09.208
Mr. Yeon, their finals are almost here,
so weekends are a must for extra lessons.

20:10.792 --> 20:13.587
[sighs] This is why we need real teachers.

20:14.922 --> 20:16.965
[mumbling] College students
have no responsibility.

20:18.091 --> 20:19.092
What about Sunday?

20:22.679 --> 20:23.722
I can do it.

20:24.264 --> 20:26.016
[woman] What time
should I put you down for?

20:27.267 --> 20:28.894
Around 1:00 p.m. or 2:00 p.m.

20:29.561 --> 20:31.063
[woman] I'll schedule you
at 2:00 p.m. then.

20:32.397 --> 20:34.733
ROLLING STOCK DRIVER'S LICENSE

20:40.364 --> 20:41.740
What's that?

20:42.366 --> 20:44.576
Someone left it
and hasn't come to get it for months.

20:45.994 --> 20:49.331
When I cover cup noodles with this,
it provides the perfect pressure.

20:50.290 --> 20:53.377
Eat dinner at my place
before you go tutoring. It's nearby.

20:53.460 --> 20:55.128
My mom makes chicken soup every day.

20:55.212 --> 20:57.422
I'm sick of it. You eat it for me.

20:58.465 --> 21:00.717
I already ate. I need more sleep.

21:03.136 --> 21:04.471
[mumbling] Geez, this chair…

21:06.556 --> 21:07.391
[student] Excuse me.

21:08.308 --> 21:11.311
Someone's sitting in Seat One.
Please tell them to switch seats.

21:11.395 --> 21:14.898
-He's sitting there because he booked it.
-It's my seat.

21:14.982 --> 21:17.359
Your one-month reservation
ended yesterday.

21:17.442 --> 21:19.194
But I've always sat there.

21:19.278 --> 21:20.487
You can't do this.

21:20.570 --> 21:22.406
He's retaking the CSAT.

21:22.489 --> 21:24.866
He came this morning
and booked Seat One for a month.

21:24.950 --> 21:27.911
[hesitates] Of all the seats,
why did he have to take mine?

21:27.995 --> 21:31.164
The one who studied there last year
got into Hanguk National University.

21:31.248 --> 21:34.251
So, that seat is popular
among my classmates.

21:35.127 --> 21:38.171
It's near the entrance,
so it's not that good. Try another seat.

21:38.255 --> 21:39.506
Go look around.

21:42.217 --> 21:43.468
[Hyeong-seok inhales sharply]

21:44.428 --> 21:45.679
[thuds loudly]

21:47.556 --> 21:50.475
It was 8:12 p.m.
That was when I paid with my card.

21:53.478 --> 21:54.313
So?

21:54.396 --> 21:57.482
That's when it would mark one month.

21:57.566 --> 21:58.775
It hasn't passed yet.

21:59.735 --> 22:03.363
You count the bookings by days,
but today's technically not over.

22:03.447 --> 22:04.781
So it means that seat…

22:04.865 --> 22:06.074
[amusing music playing]

22:06.783 --> 22:07.784
…is still mine.

22:08.368 --> 22:09.202
Uh…

22:10.287 --> 22:14.041
Since he's older and retaking the CSAT,

22:15.042 --> 22:17.002
he can have the seat for just today.

22:17.085 --> 22:18.128
I'll allow him that.

22:24.760 --> 22:25.761
Excuse me?

22:27.220 --> 22:28.055
Okay.

22:28.138 --> 22:29.765
I'll talk to him.

22:30.932 --> 22:32.559
Thank you. Oh…

22:33.477 --> 22:36.063
I'll book Seat One for a month
starting tomorrow.

22:36.146 --> 22:37.814
-My name is--
-I know.

22:37.898 --> 22:39.649
Im A-sol, the high school senior.

22:47.074 --> 22:49.117
-Geez.
-[Tae-seo sighs wearily]

22:51.578 --> 22:52.954
[cat meows]

23:10.514 --> 23:11.890
Number three is correct. Good job.

23:12.849 --> 23:15.060
-For this question, let's look here.
-[knock on door]

23:20.649 --> 23:21.483
[woman] Here.

23:22.567 --> 23:24.653
-This is for you.
-Thank you.

23:24.736 --> 23:27.072
Can you give an extra lesson
this Saturday?

23:27.823 --> 23:29.991
It's finals week. He's free all afternoon.

23:32.327 --> 23:33.578
I can do it in the evening.

23:33.662 --> 23:36.248
Oh… He goes to cram school in the evening.

23:36.832 --> 23:39.459
Uh… Should I tutor him after that?

23:40.377 --> 23:43.004
[woman] That might be too late.
Are you okay with that?

23:44.464 --> 23:45.882
[boy] When do I sleep then?

23:50.303 --> 23:52.139
-I'll get going.
-Thanks. Bye.

23:52.681 --> 23:53.598
[phone vibrates]

23:58.145 --> 24:01.398
[Eun-a] <i>Tae-seo,</i>
<i>how's 2:30 p.m. on Saturday?</i>

24:01.481 --> 24:02.566
<i>Does that work?</i>

24:07.445 --> 24:08.363
[Tae-seo] <i>Not really.</i>

24:11.449 --> 24:14.327
[Eun-a] <i>I may have to work</i>
<i>on Saturday morning.</i>

24:14.411 --> 24:17.455
<i>I'm really sorry.</i>
<i>I really need to take this job.</i>

24:20.333 --> 24:21.751
[doorbell chimes]

24:22.460 --> 24:23.378
Yes?

24:23.461 --> 24:25.755
I think I can do
an extra lesson on Saturday…

24:25.839 --> 24:27.632
-[phone vibrating]
-Excuse me. I'm sorry.

24:29.843 --> 24:31.803
HUI-SEO

24:32.512 --> 24:34.264
It was nothing. I can do it.

24:34.347 --> 24:35.599
Thank you so much.

24:36.141 --> 24:37.184
All right, then.

24:37.267 --> 24:39.936
-Okay, good night.
-Good night.

24:41.897 --> 24:43.690
[Tae-seo] Hey, Hui-seo. I was tutoring.

24:43.773 --> 24:45.984
[Hui-seo] <i>Tae-seo,</i>
<i>you better do well on your finals.</i>

24:46.067 --> 24:47.569
<i>When you got a B on your midterms,</i>

24:47.652 --> 24:50.197
<i>I was so worried</i>
<i>you'd lose your scholarship.</i>

24:50.280 --> 24:51.281
[Tae-seo] Okay.

24:52.490 --> 24:55.785
[Hui-seo sighs]
<i>I wasn't going to tell you this,</i>

24:55.869 --> 24:57.662
<i>but Grandma's knees aren't looking good.</i>

24:59.372 --> 25:03.168
<i>They said surgery would fix them,</i>
<i>but she just won't do it.</i>

25:04.794 --> 25:07.255
<i>She has the money for it,</i>
<i>but she won't use it.</i>

25:07.756 --> 25:10.300
<i>She said it's for your tuition</i>
<i>if you lose your scholarship.</i>

25:11.343 --> 25:13.261
<i>So you better ace those exams.</i>

25:14.638 --> 25:17.557
<i>Hey, Grandma is here. I'll call you back.</i>

25:17.641 --> 25:19.643
[somber music playing]

25:45.001 --> 25:46.378
[sighs]

26:00.392 --> 26:01.309
[phone vibrates]

26:04.688 --> 26:05.522
[Eun-a] <i>I'm sorry.</i>

26:10.402 --> 26:11.695
[phone vibrates]

26:12.904 --> 26:15.615
[Tae-seo] <i>It's okay.</i>
<i>I'll call you after finals are over.</i>

26:18.201 --> 26:19.369
[sighs]

26:21.454 --> 26:23.456
[gentle music playing]

26:43.476 --> 26:44.561
Tae-seo.

26:47.147 --> 26:48.231
Yes?

26:48.773 --> 26:50.442
This question…

26:51.359 --> 26:54.946
It's asking for the equation of a line
with a minimum slope.

26:55.030 --> 26:57.949
You need to find the derivative of F
like I mentioned before.

27:01.578 --> 27:02.537
[in English] Excuse me.

27:02.620 --> 27:06.166
-Which floor is the restaurant on?
-It's on the tenth floor.

27:06.791 --> 27:10.337
They are currently on a break,
and it reopens at 5:30 in the afternoon.

27:10.420 --> 27:11.755
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

27:35.820 --> 27:38.239
[in Korean] Is there a place
to see flowers near here?

27:38.323 --> 27:41.076
My daughter loves flowers.

27:41.993 --> 27:44.621
When you walk for five minutes
along the path near the beach,

27:44.704 --> 27:45.538
there's a flowerbed.

27:45.622 --> 27:48.166
-[woman] Really?
-[man] Thank you.

27:48.249 --> 27:49.667
-[Eun-a] Do you like flowers?
-Yeah.

27:51.461 --> 27:52.504
Here. It's for you.

28:13.358 --> 28:15.610
-It's this way.
-Thank you.

28:23.743 --> 28:25.078
It's a gift for you.

28:26.830 --> 28:29.332
Wow. Thank you.

28:32.836 --> 28:33.962
Thank you.

28:36.423 --> 28:37.841
[music fades]

28:54.107 --> 28:55.191
[sighs]

28:59.154 --> 29:00.447
[exhales heavily]

29:18.339 --> 29:21.426
Tae-seo. See you at the lab
during vacation.

29:24.387 --> 29:26.389
[pleasant music playing]

29:29.642 --> 29:30.477
[sighs]

29:41.321 --> 29:43.239
[Tae-seo] <i>I'm done with finals.</i>
<i>I'm leaving now.</i>

29:48.495 --> 29:50.872
<i>Let's meet up. I'll come to your hotel.</i>

30:02.675 --> 30:04.803
[Eun-a] <i>I can see you</i>
<i>for only a moment though.</i>

30:04.886 --> 30:07.806
<i>I can't meet outsiders in my uniform.</i>

30:08.681 --> 30:13.228
<i>At 2:30 p.m., I have 30 minutes,</i>
<i>so I'll get changed quickly.</i>

30:18.817 --> 30:21.986
[Tae-seo] <i>I'm on my way.</i>
<i>There's something on my mind.</i>

30:22.695 --> 30:25.865
<i>The answer is there,</i>
<i>but I have some doubt.</i>

30:26.950 --> 30:29.994
<i>When I see you,</i>
<i>I'm sure it'll become clear.</i>

30:38.253 --> 30:39.379
Eun-a?

30:39.963 --> 30:41.756
You should try this too.

30:43.967 --> 30:45.718
They're making welcome cards
for the suites.

30:45.802 --> 30:47.554
We're trying to come up
with new greetings.

30:49.222 --> 30:50.473
Are drawings okay too?

30:51.099 --> 30:52.016
What kind of drawings?

31:13.788 --> 31:14.998
Something like this.

31:15.790 --> 31:17.041
Give it a try.

31:17.125 --> 31:20.378
If it gets selected, it'll be served
with the welcome food for a month.

31:25.800 --> 31:28.177
Can I come back in 30 minutes?

31:28.261 --> 31:30.680
Do you want me to wait for 30 minutes?

31:30.763 --> 31:33.099
You drew that in a minute.
Why don't you do it now?

31:35.643 --> 31:37.312
I need to be somewhere for a moment.

32:11.012 --> 32:12.013
It's been a while.

32:12.805 --> 32:14.432
It feels like it's been years.

32:21.731 --> 32:24.233
<i>I couldn't get changed. Sorry.</i>

32:35.912 --> 32:36.955
[phone vibrates]

32:38.456 --> 32:42.335
[Tae-seo] <i>I'll be home during the break,</i>
<i>so let's see each other more often.</i>

32:43.127 --> 32:44.170
[Seong-chan] Ms. Mo Eun-a.

32:44.796 --> 32:46.381
[mellow music playing]

32:53.596 --> 32:56.099
Excuse me. Where was the exit?

32:56.182 --> 32:58.184
You can go around this way to exit.

32:59.352 --> 33:00.353
Thank you.

33:07.443 --> 33:08.361
[sighs]

33:38.224 --> 33:39.767
Was he the guy?

33:45.690 --> 33:47.400
Ms. Mo Eun-a, you can't go out in uniform…

33:52.739 --> 33:53.740
[Eun-a] Tae-seo!

33:53.823 --> 33:55.825
[Eun-a pants]

34:00.038 --> 34:01.330
I'm sorry!

34:02.540 --> 34:03.374
[sighs]

34:24.479 --> 34:25.605
[phone vibrates]

34:26.355 --> 34:28.524
[Eun-a] <i>You always have the right answer</i>

34:29.984 --> 34:32.320
<i>because you don't jump to conclusions.</i>

34:33.196 --> 34:35.406
<i>You don't do anything</i>
<i>just for the sake of it.</i>

34:51.172 --> 34:52.882
You came back exactly in 30 minutes.

34:55.802 --> 35:00.681
Here. I liked your corn drawing.

35:02.683 --> 35:04.143
I'll draw it now.

35:11.943 --> 35:15.613
Your resume said
you majored in early childhood education.

35:16.239 --> 35:18.699
I guess that's why
the way you treat people is different.

35:19.117 --> 35:22.995
Mmm… How should I say it?
You're filled with affection.

35:24.372 --> 35:25.373
I am?

35:27.458 --> 35:28.584
Thank you.

35:59.615 --> 36:00.700
Sir.

36:01.576 --> 36:02.827
I'm getting off.

36:04.078 --> 36:05.079
Sir!

36:08.499 --> 36:10.501
[soft emotional music playing]

36:24.182 --> 36:25.474
[driver] Aren't you getting off?

36:27.685 --> 36:29.478
No, it's fine.

36:45.077 --> 36:46.746
Get a job after graduating?

36:49.415 --> 36:53.085
Honestly, studying for four years
has already been a luxury for me.

36:56.380 --> 36:57.381
I see.

36:58.799 --> 37:02.803
You want what you have to do,
not what you like to do.

37:03.846 --> 37:04.722
[exhales heavily]

37:06.182 --> 37:08.768
That's strong. It resonates with me.

37:11.979 --> 37:12.980
[inhales deeply]

37:14.148 --> 37:16.776
You sure you won't regret it?
I'm already sad.

37:17.652 --> 37:18.945
I'm not the type to look back.

37:26.494 --> 37:29.288
Can I wrap things up
and close the lab today?

37:50.518 --> 37:52.520
[somber music playing]

38:20.673 --> 38:26.429
JULY

38:30.641 --> 38:33.394
Interns can move into the residence hall.

38:33.477 --> 38:36.105
Why wait? I'm going to move in right away.

38:38.441 --> 38:40.109
So you're going to live there then?

38:40.192 --> 38:43.529
If you have a big bag like a suitcase,
could you lend it to me?

38:43.612 --> 38:45.531
I've never traveled before.

38:45.614 --> 38:46.449
I need to pack.

38:47.575 --> 38:50.411
-You can use mine.
-[Seon-gyu] Would that be okay?

38:53.122 --> 38:55.875
So what will it be, Eun-a?

38:55.958 --> 38:57.460
Want to borrow my suitcase?

38:57.960 --> 38:59.795
Tell me
since you're the one who'll use it.

39:00.504 --> 39:01.672
Could I borrow it?

39:01.756 --> 39:04.300
Silver, black, white, or yellow?

39:04.383 --> 39:05.384
Which one?

39:06.260 --> 39:07.470
The biggest one.

39:07.553 --> 39:11.098
The biggest one. Okay.

39:29.658 --> 39:30.868
[knock on door]

39:47.760 --> 39:48.844
[door closes]

39:54.892 --> 39:56.018
[sighs]

40:03.067 --> 40:04.110
[door thuds]

40:15.121 --> 40:18.124
I would've prepared a better breakfast
if you had told me earlier.

40:19.375 --> 40:20.960
I actually wanted pine nut porridge.

40:25.631 --> 40:28.926
-What about your wedding?
-[chuckles dryly] What wedding?

40:29.009 --> 40:30.678
What? You made a big fuss about it.

40:32.888 --> 40:34.223
We'll live together first.

40:34.890 --> 40:36.517
She might run away.

40:36.600 --> 40:38.394
If she does,
I should make it easy for her.

40:40.104 --> 40:42.481
I don't understand grown-ups.

40:47.736 --> 40:50.197
What? You don't like that I'm leaving?

40:51.615 --> 40:53.242
[clicks tongue, chuckles softly]

40:53.826 --> 40:55.286
When did you grow up so fast?

40:56.412 --> 40:57.746
I've done nothing for you.

40:59.707 --> 41:01.250
You gave me a lot of love.

41:02.960 --> 41:05.421
Yes, I did that more than anyone.

41:06.213 --> 41:07.798
You regained your health,

41:08.757 --> 41:11.510
so I decided to go to college
in the summer of my senior year.

41:11.594 --> 41:14.847
When college wasn't my thing,
I found another path.

41:14.930 --> 41:16.557
It's all thanks to you.

41:22.229 --> 41:24.231
[soft emotional music playing]

41:24.815 --> 41:25.858
I'll… [voice cracking]

41:26.525 --> 41:28.402
I'll be all right,

41:29.487 --> 41:30.905
so go enjoy your life.

41:32.281 --> 41:33.532
Live as if you're on a journey.

41:36.202 --> 41:37.578
Just do all the things you want.

41:42.833 --> 41:43.834
I'll do that.

41:46.128 --> 41:48.839
You know I'll never waste
the time you've given me.

41:58.682 --> 42:00.893
-Does it taste good?
-Dad, you're the best.

42:06.607 --> 42:07.900
[exhales heavily]

42:16.200 --> 42:17.701
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
YEON TAE-SEO

42:26.627 --> 42:28.254
[knock on door]

42:39.265 --> 42:43.060
I didn't tell your dad about that boy.

42:43.143 --> 42:46.188
You can tell him. He knows we're close.

42:47.606 --> 42:49.108
[zipper hisses]

42:50.484 --> 42:53.362
Seong-chan told me
you're good at your work.

42:59.910 --> 43:00.953
[So-hyeon sighs]

43:03.664 --> 43:06.875
Don't ever leave Dad by himself.

43:07.501 --> 43:08.711
Even if he's healthy now,

43:11.046 --> 43:12.047
don't ever do it.

43:14.508 --> 43:15.634
I'll stick close to him.

43:21.765 --> 43:26.395
ROOM 407

43:26.478 --> 43:28.731
JEONG JAE-WON
MO EUN-A

43:37.114 --> 43:38.240
[door lock beeps]

43:45.539 --> 43:47.541
[gentle music playing]

44:11.190 --> 44:12.608
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
YEON TAE-SEO

44:29.833 --> 44:31.210
[phone vibrates]

44:35.631 --> 44:38.384
[Seong-chan] <i>It's a job posting</i>
<i>for an overseas internship next year.</i>

44:38.467 --> 44:42.054
<i>You'll have a good shot at it</i>
<i>once you build your career here.</i>

44:42.137 --> 44:43.806
<i>Just study English in your spare time.</i>

44:44.807 --> 44:47.685
<i>I hope this will help you</i>
<i>stand on your own.</i>

44:56.568 --> 45:00.656
CAFETERIA HOURS DURING SUMMER VACATION

45:04.410 --> 45:05.369
[camera shutter clicks]

45:19.967 --> 45:23.387
[Tae-seo] <i>I'll get home at 2:00 p.m.</i>
<i>When do you want to meet?</i>

45:27.850 --> 45:29.852
[objects clattering]

45:31.228 --> 45:32.062
[wood thuds]

45:33.814 --> 45:35.816
Grandpa, the light will work fine now.

45:36.483 --> 45:38.444
Okay. [chuckles]

45:41.113 --> 45:43.115
Grandma should see a doctor.

45:44.116 --> 45:46.952
She won't.
There's no point in telling her.

45:48.287 --> 45:51.874
I'll make an appointment.
You should take her.

45:55.335 --> 45:56.420
[Chang-sik] Geez.

45:56.503 --> 45:59.715
I worry the roof will collapse
during the monsoon.

45:59.798 --> 46:01.550
All the firewood will get wet.

46:01.633 --> 46:05.179
I get paid monthly
for renting out the storage.

46:06.096 --> 46:08.182
It's only a few tens of thousands of won,

46:08.265 --> 46:11.268
but I have to make sure
this gets passed on to Hui-seo later.

46:15.564 --> 46:17.691
I'll take that to mean
she'll go to the hospital.

46:22.863 --> 46:24.156
[machine whirring]

46:24.239 --> 46:29.495
YEONWOO WOODWORKING STUDIO

46:31.205 --> 46:32.539
-Hello.
-Hey.

46:34.583 --> 46:36.293
[whirring stops]

46:36.376 --> 46:37.794
What brings you here, Tae-seo?

46:37.878 --> 46:39.463
I'm on break, so I'm visiting.

46:39.546 --> 46:43.050
Grandpa's worried
the wood will get wet during the monsoon.

46:43.133 --> 46:44.384
He wants something to cover it.

46:44.468 --> 46:47.304
Ah. That roof looks like it would leak,
but it never does.

46:47.387 --> 46:50.974
But I'll get you something tomorrow
that will cover the whole thing.

46:51.058 --> 46:52.226
Thank you.

46:52.309 --> 46:54.603
I don't think it'll leak either.

46:54.686 --> 46:58.023
But I guess he's so worried
he can't even sleep.

46:58.690 --> 46:59.942
That's not it.

47:00.025 --> 47:02.945
Anyway, you should hurry
and get your military service done.

47:03.028 --> 47:04.821
That's all he talks about when he's drunk.

47:04.905 --> 47:07.741
If something happens to them
when you're in the military,

47:07.824 --> 47:09.910
he's so worried Hui-seo will be all alone.

47:11.453 --> 47:14.957
You can enlist early these days.
Hurry and get it over with.

47:17.417 --> 47:19.419
[pensive music playing]

47:43.360 --> 47:50.325
I'LL GET HOME AT 2:00 P.M.
WHEN DO YOU WANT TO MEET?

47:56.456 --> 47:58.917
[sighs] It's so hot.

48:00.252 --> 48:01.837
Staying at the hotel would be better.

48:03.672 --> 48:05.382
The schedule changes all the time.

48:07.509 --> 48:08.719
We're always on standby.

48:11.013 --> 48:12.639
Can you believe the AC's broken?

48:13.599 --> 48:14.808
[groans]

48:14.891 --> 48:17.811
Aren't you hot, Eun-a?
Should I make the fan turn?

48:17.894 --> 48:19.521
No, they'll fly away.

48:21.857 --> 48:24.067
You're still working on the welcome cards?

48:26.653 --> 48:29.031
I'm making them
with the writing and drawing this time.

48:29.114 --> 48:30.324
The writing is the hard part.

48:31.325 --> 48:33.535
I wasn't selected
when I only did the drawings.

48:37.080 --> 48:38.081
I'll get it this time.

48:39.625 --> 48:41.710
WELCOME TO OUR HOTEL
WHERE YOU CAN SEE THE OCEAN

48:41.793 --> 48:44.087
ENJOY THE LAID-BACK VIBE
OF GANGWON AT OUR HOTEL

48:44.171 --> 48:46.173
[solemn music playing]

48:47.174 --> 48:48.675
[mumbling] "Welcome…"

49:03.774 --> 49:10.530
I'LL GET HOME AT 2:00 P.M.
WHEN DO YOU WANT TO MEET?

49:17.162 --> 49:18.664
[phone vibrates]

49:24.961 --> 49:27.547
I'm home. When do you get off work?

49:30.550 --> 49:32.135
I'm in the dorms.

49:33.804 --> 49:34.638
I see.

49:35.889 --> 49:36.807
You moved in.

49:37.474 --> 49:38.767
[Eun-a] <i>I was going to tell you,</i>

49:39.476 --> 49:41.311
<i>but I moved in</i>
<i>as soon as I became an intern,</i>

49:41.395 --> 49:42.771
<i>so it was hectic.</i>

49:46.066 --> 49:47.109
Right.

49:50.987 --> 49:53.740
Do you have time? I'll come over.

49:54.408 --> 49:55.534
<i>It's a quick bus ride.</i>

49:58.704 --> 50:02.499
<i>If now isn't a good time,</i>
<i>I can see you in the evening.</i>

50:03.041 --> 50:05.210
-Today, I…
-[door opens]

50:16.138 --> 50:17.681
[sighs] Don't come, Tae-seo.

50:20.392 --> 50:22.602
I mean today. Don't come today.

50:25.647 --> 50:28.817
-I'll be there tomorrow.
-[Eun-a] <i>No, not tomorrow either.</i>

50:33.488 --> 50:34.906
When are you coming home?

50:35.991 --> 50:39.244
[Eun-a] <i>I can't.</i>
<i>Like I said, I live here now.</i>

50:43.039 --> 50:45.459
<i>Tae-seo, the thing is…</i>

50:47.794 --> 50:50.922
[Tae-seo] <i>I'm going back to Seoul</i>
<i>the day after tomorrow to tutor.</i>

50:51.006 --> 50:53.216
Let's try to work out our schedules again.

51:00.849 --> 51:02.476
Don't.

51:04.728 --> 51:08.523
<i>Let's stop forcing our schedules to match.</i>

51:09.566 --> 51:11.902
<i>This time is so precious to lose for me.</i>

51:12.527 --> 51:14.654
<i>I want to make use of it all.</i>

51:17.073 --> 51:21.787
I've found something I want to do,
and it matters a lot to me.

51:22.370 --> 51:25.290
<i>I just need to do it.</i>
<i>I really want to excel at it.</i>

51:25.957 --> 51:28.460
<i>You should stop wasting time</i>
<i>going back and forth.</i>

51:28.543 --> 51:30.045
<i>Spend the time on yourself.</i>

51:30.754 --> 51:33.215
<i>Let's not waste</i>
<i>a single moment of our time.</i>

51:43.391 --> 51:44.392
Well…

51:45.393 --> 51:47.187
[sighs] I mean…

51:47.979 --> 51:49.689
[Tae-seo] <i>I don't know what you're saying…</i>

51:53.610 --> 51:54.903
But why can I understand it?

52:00.283 --> 52:02.160
Why do I get it all?

52:17.884 --> 52:18.927
Okay.

52:27.602 --> 52:28.645
Let's do that.

52:45.620 --> 52:46.621
<i>That's what we'll do.</i>

53:07.809 --> 53:10.687
[sentimental music playing]

54:12.499 --> 54:14.292
[Da-jeong]
This vegetable drawing is so cute.

54:14.376 --> 54:16.670
Yes. The corn is so adorable.

54:18.171 --> 54:20.048
Did you draw this, Eun-a?

54:21.549 --> 54:22.550
Yes.

54:23.301 --> 54:26.471
[Da-jeong] I think the writing fits
our hotel's image better too.

54:51.788 --> 54:54.165
[Tae-seo] <i>You like people,</i>
<i>you're good at English,</i>

54:54.249 --> 54:55.583
<i>and you draw vegetables well.</i>

54:56.251 --> 54:58.712
I know there's a job out there
you can give your all to.

54:59.963 --> 55:01.089
It'll work out

55:02.882 --> 55:04.759
in ways we never imagined.

55:07.470 --> 55:10.974
We'll know for sure what that is
once we become adults.

55:13.518 --> 55:14.519
[Eun-a] <i>You were right.</i>

55:16.354 --> 55:18.023
<i>In ways we never imagined,</i>

55:19.816 --> 55:20.817
<i>we…</i>

55:25.739 --> 55:27.741
[music continues]

56:45.401 --> 56:52.367
DECEMBER

56:56.412 --> 56:58.289
[music ends]

56:58.373 --> 57:00.792
[engine revs, sputters]

57:00.875 --> 57:03.628
-[engine revving]
-[grunts]

57:03.711 --> 57:08.007
-[ignition clicks]
-[engine revs, stops]

57:09.968 --> 57:11.094
[Chang-sik] Goodness.

57:11.886 --> 57:14.389
Is it because the weather's cold?

57:14.472 --> 57:18.768
[sighs exasperatedly] No one's picking up
because it's too early in the day.

57:18.852 --> 57:19.936
What do we do?

57:20.019 --> 57:22.063
We need help.

57:22.147 --> 57:25.442
-It's okay. I can ride the bus.
-[Hwa-sun] Aren't you going to be late?

57:25.525 --> 57:27.944
And you need to shave your head
before going to boot camp.

57:28.027 --> 57:29.404
-I'll make it if I go now.
-[Hwa-sun] What?

57:29.487 --> 57:31.906
-[Tae-seo] I'll get going. Don't come.
-[Hwa-sun] Oh, no. Goodness.

57:31.990 --> 57:33.700
-[Chang-sik] You can't go like this.
-I'll go.

57:33.783 --> 57:35.660
-Oh? Hey.
-[Hwa-sun exclaims]

57:35.743 --> 57:36.870
[Chang-sik] Oh!

57:36.953 --> 57:38.413
-Goodness, are you all right?
-Gosh.

57:38.496 --> 57:41.875
-[Chang-sik] Gosh, dear!
-[Hwa-sun] Tae-seo. What about him?

57:45.295 --> 57:47.464
[Hui-seo panting]

57:53.386 --> 57:54.846
Go back. It's slippery.

57:55.889 --> 57:57.056
Just go then.

58:00.768 --> 58:01.603
Don't get hurt.

58:04.355 --> 58:05.356
Don't you dare get hurt.

58:08.943 --> 58:10.069
I'll get going.

58:19.662 --> 58:21.664
[breathing heavily]

58:27.795 --> 58:29.797
[slow instrumental music playing]

58:42.644 --> 58:44.896
[Tae-seo] <i>I used to hate</i>
<i>thinking about the next step.</i>

58:46.314 --> 58:48.233
<i>But I started to think about the future</i>

58:49.692 --> 58:51.277
<i>because of what you would always say.</i>

58:53.905 --> 58:57.033
Where we'll be, what we'll do,
and with who…

59:03.456 --> 59:05.542
[Tae-seo] <i>It made me curious</i>
<i>about my future.</i>

59:06.960 --> 59:08.419
<i>About myself.</i>

59:10.713 --> 59:13.841
<i>About what I wanted and what I could do.</i>

59:18.346 --> 59:22.058
<i>The countless worries about the future</i>
<i>began with you.</i>

59:24.143 --> 59:26.563
<i>And they ended</i>
<i>with the expressions on your face,</i>

59:27.313 --> 59:30.733
<i>your responses, and your answers.</i>

59:32.151 --> 59:33.486
<i>I realize that now.</i>

59:39.534 --> 59:43.538
<i>Without you, I lose interest in myself.</i>

59:52.755 --> 59:56.551
<i>I have no curiosity about myself.</i>

59:58.886 --> 01:00:03.349
<i>That makes me scared and sad.</i>

01:00:07.312 --> 01:00:10.064
<i>Where we'll be, what we'll do…</i>

01:00:13.067 --> 01:00:14.068
<i>and with who…</i>

01:00:15.820 --> 01:00:18.698
-[music fades]
-[train honk echoing]

01:00:18.781 --> 01:00:25.747
SEPTEMBER, 10 YEARS LATER

01:01:13.127 --> 01:01:15.421
[driver] <i>The train will depart now.</i>
<i>The doors are closing.</i>

01:01:15.505 --> 01:01:18.007
[indistinct announcement over PA]

01:01:28.142 --> 01:01:30.269
Doors closed. Screen doors closed.

01:01:30.353 --> 01:01:31.729
Train departing.

01:01:35.483 --> 01:01:37.485
[emotional music playing]

01:01:55.420 --> 01:01:58.923
STILL SHINING

01:02:28.411 --> 01:02:30.413
Subtitle translation by: Hye Won Yoon
